def: Fossil fruit; a fruit petrified; a carpolite.

An instrument for measuring the distance which one has traveledon the road; an odometer, pedometer, or perambulator.The waywiser to a coach, exactly measuring the miles, and showingthem by an index. Evelyn.
A small dog; -- written also fise, fyce, fiste, etc. [SouthernU.S.]

The process by which miners seek to discover metallic lodes. Itconsist in sinking small pits through the superficial deposits to thesolid rock, and then driving from one pit to another across thedirection of the vein, in such manner as to cross all the veinsbetween the two pits.
The six-shafted bird of paradise. See Paradise bird, underParadise.
A mass of type confusedly mixed or unsorted. [Written alsopie.]
A calculous concretion, especially one in the kidneys orbladder; the disease arising from a calculus.
The lengthening of a syllable from short to long.
A shop or barroom where gin is sold as a beverage. [Colloq.]
